New world screwworm (_Cochliomyia hominivorax_), Panama
-----------------------------------------------
Information received on 18 May 2012 from Dr Manuel Antonio Gonzalez Cano, Delegate, Direccion de Salud Animal, Ministerio de Desarrollo Agropecuario, Panama city, Panama

Summary

Epidemiology
Report type Immediate notification
Start date 11 Feb 2012
Date of 1st confirmation of the event 28 Apr 2012
Report date 18 May 2012
Date submitted to OIE 18 May 2012
Reason for notification Unexpected increase in morbidity or mortality of a listed disease

Summary description In Panama, new world screwworm (_Cochliomyia hominivorax_) is present in the province of Darien with 5 to 7 cases per year. During the 1st 5 months of 2012, 15 cases were observed.

Manifestation of disease Clinical disease
Causal agent Larvae of _Cochliomyia hominivorax_
This event pertains to a defined zone within the country

Source of the outbreak(s) or origin of infection - Unknown or inconclusive

Epidemiological comments An epidemiological investigation was carried out on farms within a 5-km radius of the positive cases, with inspection of susceptible animals. Five percent coumaphos powder was distributed, to be applied to wounds, as well as collection tubes (alcohol 95 percent) for myiasis sample collection (6 tubes).

Movement control measures have been implemented through checkpoints (Torti, Panama and Agua Fria, Darien). All animals are being inspected and treated. Sterile flies have been released, and the dose for eradication is being maintained in the affected area (6000 flies/nautical mile).

Increased Distribution - Disease Impact
Increased Incidence
Total Panama
Species Cattle
Change 0=>1

Increased Incidence
Total Darien
Species Cattle
Change 1=>5

Control measures - Measures applied

Control of arthropods
Movement control inside the country
Zoning
Disinfection of infected premises/establishment(s)
No vaccination
Treatment of affected animals (coumaphos is being applied to wounds)

Measures to be applied - No other measures

Laboratory name and type COPEG (Commission Panama-United States for the Eradication and Prevention of NSW) (OIE's Reference Laboratory)

Species Cattle
Test entomological investigations
Test date 28 Apr 2012
Result Positive

Species Cattle
Test entomological investigations
Test date 6 May 2012
Result Positive

Future Reporting
The event is continuing. Weekly follow-up reports will be submitted.

